-- Location/Address Listing - Detailed instructions
((SELECT id FROM categories WHERE name = 'BMO Locations'), '8.2', 'Location/Address Listing - A file must be completed for each location indicated in sections 8.0.1 and 8.0.4. You can do the following for the locations listed below. For each location/address answer all required questions: Add new locations by clicking the Add button, Edit an existing location by clicking on the list, Do not delete any locations. If they are no longer used set their status to Inactive, Do not use Inactive or any other you have changed or added in the current session only, Please review the information within the location object by clicking on Edit and make any updates as necessary. Existing locations being entered should reflect all previous controls that were last attested to. When entering existing or new Third-Party or Subcontractor locations it is encouraged to reach out to building management and/or the Third-Party or Subcontractor''s internal Physical Security department to ensure Physical Security controls are accurately captured. Failure to provide sufficient controls will result in UNSATISFACTORY or NEEDS IMPROVEMENT ratings and mitigation will be required via control implementation. When entering a location all fields are mandatory. Failure to provide a response to all location fields will result in an UNSATISFACTORY or NEEDS IMPROVEMENT ratings.', 'Detailed instructions for location management including Corporate Headquarters and Woodridge Software locations with specific requirements for editing, status management, and mandatory field completion', 'location address listing file completed sections add new locations edit existing delete status inactive review information mandatory fields corporate headquarters woodridge software physical security controls unsatisfactory needs improvement ratings mitigation'),

